{"id": 237081744, "title": "King of Reggaet\u00f3n' Don Omar's cancer bombshell in emotional Instagram post", "text": "Puerto Rican rapper, singer-songwriter, record producer and actor, Don Omar, has revealed that he is suffering from cancer in an emotional Instagram post. The star is known as the 'King of Reggaet\u00f3n' by music critics and fans alike, and the news has come as a shock to many. In the post he shared on Monday, June 17, he wrote: \"Yes today but tomorrow I will be cancer free. Good intentions are well received. See you all soon. #f***cancer.\" The post was initially written in Spanish, but it has been translated to English. In the image he is seen wearing a hospital wristband from Orlando Health, a private, not-for-profit network of community and specialty hospitals based in Orlando, Florida. READ MORE: Lewis Capaldi teases epic music comeback as he's pictured for first time in a year Billboard report that the news came just hours after the Puerto Rican artist (real name William Omar Landr\u00f3n Rivera) posted a video of a group of dancers auditioning for the second leg of his Back to Reggaet\u00f3n Tour. He wrote in the post that 'people dared to dream' with him. He said: \"The most special thing about today\u2019s auditions is seeing that there are people who want to dare to dream with me. Thank you to each of you who gave your all on the dance floor! This second stage of the tour comes with everything.\" Alternative text: The image below is shared from Instagram. It shows Don Omar's wrist with a hospital wristband. It is captioned: \"\"Yes today but tomorrow I will be cancer free. Good intentions are well received. See you all soon. #f***cancer.\" The \u201cPobre Diabla\u201d singer, who made his highly awaited comeback with his 2023 album Forever King, went on tour in the spring with a 20-date stretch that ran from March 7 to April 21, finishing off at the Kaseya Center in Miami. Support has streamed in for the singer, with many artists sending their well wishes on social media. Mexican American rapper, Snow Tha Product wrote: \"[sic] Love u! [sic] Praying for you man\" Puerto Rican Singer Ozuna, who has over 23 million followers on Instagram wrote: \"Much strength black that God is with you\" (this comment was translated from Spanish). Efra\u00edn David Fines Nevares, known professionally as Tito El Bambino, is a Puerto Rican singer and songwriter who rose to fame as part of the duo H\u00e9ctor & Tito commented: \"God is in Control!\"", "summary": "The \u201cPobre Diabla\u201d singer, who made his highly awaited comeback with his 2023 album Forever King, went on tour in the spring finishing off at the Kaseya Center in Miami", "url": "https://www.mirror.co.uk/3am/celebrity-news/king-reggaetn-don-omar-shares-33051839", "image": "https://i2-prod.ok.co.uk/incoming/article33051843.ece/ALTERNATES/s1200/0_Don-Omar.jpg", "video": null, "publish_date": "2024-06-18 00:37:47", "author": "Zasha Whiteway-Wilkinson", "authors": ["Zasha Whiteway-Wilkinson"], "language": "en", "catgory": "politics", "source_country": "gb", "sentiment": 0.086}